<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,310,758,784]" box="[189,310,758,784]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,758,784]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,758,784]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,805,937]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,459,805,831]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,459,805,831]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Polygala tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[469,562,806,832]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[724,915,805,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosperma">
<emphasis box="[724,742,806,831]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[759,915,805,831]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">trichosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from it by its internal sepals (wings) with two glands near the rounded apex, and convergent ring of trichomes at the base of the seed (vs internal sepals without glands and with acute apex, and divergent ring of trichomes at the base of the seed in 
<taxonomicName box="[279,463,911,937]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosperma">
<emphasis box="[279,463,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P. trichosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="137" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,324,976,1002]" box="[189,324,976,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,976,1002]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,976,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,1023,1190]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
The specific epithet is a reference to 
<collectingRegion box="[611,789,1023,1049]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Tocantins State</collectingRegion>
where the species is endemic. Two phytogeographic domains of the state, the Amazon and the Cerrado, are known for large areas of vegetation in a good conservation status. Even though new species from 
<collectingRegion box="[812,926,1093,1119]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
are being continuously described (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Araujo D. &amp; Antar G. M. &amp; Lombardi J. A." box="[189,406,1128,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="27 - 32" refId="ref5946" refString="Araujo D., Antar G. M. &amp; Lombardi J. A. 2016. Dioscorea compacta (Dioscoreaceae), a new endangered dwarf species from the Jalapao region, Tocantins, Brazil. Kew Bulletin 71: 27 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 016 - 9635 - 8" type="journal article" year="2016">
Araújo 
<emphasis box="[278,329,1128,1154]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moreira A. L. C. &amp; Antar G. M. &amp; Simao-Bianchini R. &amp; Cavalcanti T. B." box="[418,647,1128,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="146 - 152" refId="ref7020" refString="Moreira A. L. C., Antar G. M., Simao-Bianchini R. &amp; Cavalcanti T. B. 2017. Contribution to the knowledge of Bonamia (Convolvulaceae) in Brazil: a new species and a new occurrence. Phytotaxa 306: 146 - 152. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 306.2.4" type="journal article" year="2017">
Moreira 
<emphasis box="[520,571,1128,1154]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa-Silva R. G. &amp; Antar G. M." box="[660,998,1128,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="38 - 46" refId="ref6132" refString="Barbosa-Silva R. G. &amp; Antar G. M. 2020. Description vs deforestation: Couepia brevistaminea (Chrysobalanaceae), a new species on the frontier of agricultural expansion in the Brazilian savanna. Phytotaxa 471 (1): 38 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 471.1.4" type="journal article" year="2020">Barbosa-Silva &amp; Antar 2020</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Silva O. L. M. &amp; Antar G. M. &amp; Riina R. &amp; Cordeiro I." box="[1010,1206,1128,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="131 - 136" refId="ref7687" refString="Silva O. L. M., Antar G. M., Riina R. &amp; Cordeiro I. 2020. Euphorbia adenoplicata, a new species of Euphorbia sect. Crossadenia from Brazil. Systematic Botany 45 (1): 131 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364420 X 15801369352388" type="journal article" year="2020">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[1077,1129,1128,1154]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
), the flora of the state is relatively poorly known (
<bibRefCitation author="BFG &amp; The Brazil Flora Group" box="[574,700,1163,1190]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="1085 - 1113" refId="ref6305" refString="BFG - The Brazil Flora Group 2015. Growing knowledge: an overview of seed plant knowledge in Brazil. Rodriguesia 66: 1085 - 1113. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201566411" type="journal article" year="2015">BFG 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and more collecting efforts are in order.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
